<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="English" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">English,</orth> adj. pertaining to England: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 3, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.299" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 299</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.6.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 8</bibl> Very often in the Histories (<cit><quote>E. John,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>E. Henry,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 1, 36</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 66</bibl>. <cit><quote>E. John Talbot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 3</bibl></cit>. 30).<lb />Substantively, 1) the English language: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 6</bibl> <cit><quote>(the king's E.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 143</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.142" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.142" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 142</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.160" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.121" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 121</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 15</bibl>.
<lb />2) the English people or army: <bibl n="shak. mv 2.8.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 8, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 5.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 3, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 81</bibl>. Very often in the Histories, f. i.: <cit><quote>fly, noble E.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 4, 10</bibl></cit>. Sometimes == Englishmen: <cit><quote>when E. measure backward their own ground,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 3</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the blood of E. shall manure the ground,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 137</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a power of E.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 22</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 98</bibl>. cf. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.111" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 104</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>